 "cells": [
  {

   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Plot Levelset Example"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "834f337d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Imports"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "24c42b40",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stderr",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "2025-08-05 15:11:56,493 \t DEBUG \t CRISTAL.__init__.<module> \t CRISTAL version 0.0.1 (date: 2025-08-01) loaded successfully.\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "\n",
    "from cristal import DyCF, DyCFPlotter, IMPLEMENTED_REGULARIZATION_OPTIONS\n",
    "from cristal.utils.data import make_T_rotated"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "0acc7efe",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Parameters"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "b3657d5c",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "d = 2  # Data dimension\n",
    "n = 8  # Degree of the polynomial basis\n",
    "N = 1000  # Number of samples"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "7499003f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Data"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "94e9bc9b",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "data = make_T_rotated(N)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "bb4c4167",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Without regularization for DyCF\n",
    "Show the **Christoffel function** level sets"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ff101fdb",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Fit the Christoffel function"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "1974030f",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "<cristal.christoffel.DyCF at 0x21436d84ec0>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 4,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "dycf = DyCF(n, IMPLEMENTED_REGULARIZATION_OPTIONS.CONSTANT)\n",
    "dycf.fit(data)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "9d21f1bd",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Plot the level set"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "4d2c4491",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "plotter = DyCFPlotter(dycf)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "7b6a4f17",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plotter.levelset(data, n_x1=500, n_x2=500, levels=[45, 512, 2000], percentiles=[50, 75])\n",
    "# n_x1 and n_x2 control the resolution of the grid for plotting\n",
    "# You can adjust the levels and percentiles as needed\n",
    "# More information can be found in the odds_optimized.plotter.LevelsetPlotter.plot documentation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ea023d63",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Plot the boundary decision\n",
    "Only outliers because the regularization is not set."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "b4f465a7",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plotter.boundary(data, n_x1=500, n_x2=500)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b84c3549",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Using \"comb\" regularization for DyCF\n",
    "**\"comb\"** regularization means that the **level set of DyCF at 1** is equivalent to the level set of the **Christoffel function at $\\begin{pmatrix}n+d \\\\ d\\end{pmatrix}$**, where **d** is the number of **features** and **n** is the **degree** of the polynomial."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f26dee8b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Fit the Christoffel function"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "id": "b61c8073",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "<cristal.christoffel.DyCF at 0x21440ce3890>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 8,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "dycf_comb = DyCF(n, IMPLEMENTED_REGULARIZATION_OPTIONS.COMB)\n",
    "dycf_comb.fit(data)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "d95f2275",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Plot the level set"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "id": "728bb457",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "plotter_comb = DyCFPlotter(dycf_comb)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "id": "3ee47011",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plotter_comb.levelset(data, n_x1=500, n_x2=500, levels=[10, 500, 2000], percentiles=[50, 75])\n",
    "# n_x1 and n_x2 control the resolution of the grid for plotting\n",
    "# You can adjust the levels and percentiles as needed\n",
    "# More information can be found in the odds_optimized.plotter.LevelsetPlotter.plot documentation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "53ad263a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Plot the boundary decision"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "id": "fcf542ba",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plotter_comb.boundary(data, n_x1=500, n_x2=500)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "c663d880",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Using \"vu_C\" regularization for DyCF\n",
    "**\"vu_C\"** regularization means that the **level set of DyCF at 1** is equivalent to the level set of the **Christoffel function at** $\\mathbf{\\frac{n^{3d/2}}{C}}$, where **d** is the number of **features** and **n** is the **degree** of the polynomial."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "825eef01",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Fit the Christoffel function"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "id": "85868d9c",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "<cristal.christoffel.DyCF at 0x2143e0a8e10>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 12,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "dycf_vu_C = DyCF(n, regularization=IMPLEMENTED_REGULARIZATION_OPTIONS.VU_C)\n",
    "dycf_vu_C.fit(data)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b661712a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Plot the level set"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "id": "fb7397f5",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "plotter_vu_C = DyCFPlotter(dycf_vu_C)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "id": "36f13f2a",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plotter_vu_C.levelset(data, n_x1=500, n_x2=500, levels=[10, 500, 2000], percentiles=[50, 75])\n",
    "# n_x1 and n_x2 control the resolution of the grid for plotting\n",
    "# You can adjust the levels and percentiles as needed\n",
    "# More information can be found in the odds_optimized.plotter.LevelsetPlotter.plot documentation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "64bd5482",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Plot the boundary decision"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 15,
   "id": "3ba7db51",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 640x480 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plotter_vu_C.boundary(data, n_x1=500, n_x2=500)"
   ]
  }
 ],
